<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105780" target="top"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/zmorse/pics/Khallim2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=traxxeq>traxxeq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/03 1:26:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5150.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 52 DWF Warrior - I hate to do this...</span><hr size=1> Keep the dirk, sell the bloodpoint and buy a captian's mallet for your offhand.  Thats what I'd do. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.webspacesales.com/traxxeq/traxx2.bmp" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=414053" target="top">The stuff I could get.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilaxin>Kilaxin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/03 12:24:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5150.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 52 DWF Warrior - I hate to do this...</span><hr size=1> Get a frostbringer and an anklesmasher (or whatever that 10/20 thing is that procs snare).<br>
<br>
Wavecrasher is another option but those can be hard to find/pricey, although they are pretty decent aggro.<br>
<br>
However, since you said you don't have crazy cash i'd go for a frostbringer, sell your bloodpoint or croaking dirk (whichever will get you more money) and buy the anklesmasher, then sell the other weapon.<br>
<br>
If there's no proc you really wont get much aggro from it, unfortunately, at least that's what i've experienced. Also, i'm not sure what your style of play is, but until you get epics/CHSD/Willsapper or whatever, weapons wont produce any real aggro, so just go for DPS if you have the cash. If you happen to get lucky i'd say get two fleshgrinders, but that doesn't really look like it's on the table for you at the moment. Ah well, whatever, good luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://kupo.homestead.com/files/Kilaxin_sig01.png"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scarsoulklaw>ScarSoulKlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/03 1:29:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5150.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 52 DWF Warrior - I hate to do this...</span><hr size=1> Are you looking for Agro weapons, DPS weapons, buzzword weapons, or something that's utilitarian enough that you won't be swapping weapons every 5 minutes?<br>
<br>
You don't list whether or not you're in a guild or your haste, which would have really helped us make recommendations here.<br>
<br>
Off the cuff, at level 52?  Sell the Croaking Dirk and get the FB if you can.  Keep the BloodPoint for now.<br>
<br>
At 52, the 10/21 ratio is fine for what you'll be facing.  The proc isn't agro but it's certainly DPS and whatever procs you get will add up to healing you don't need from others.<br>
<br>
Just remember that you'll probably be using the FB primary.  In that situation, you'll be 12/22 primary and 10/21 offhand.  <br>
<br>
If you want a little added agro, another sword for your consideration is the BBoT (Blade Blade of Tormenting) from Kael.  9/22 with a proc that has a nice way of pissing off most mobs (small DD, short DoT and some counters for agro).  This tends to be really cheap these days and is a very undervalued weapon for young warriors.<br>
<br>
Another agro weapon to consider would be the quest sword from Sanctu Seru - procs a melee debuff that unless you have a Shaman higher than level 29 doing their melee debuffs constantly would serve you fine.  It's an easy quest, one mob to kill who really isn't that hard.<br>
<br>
Depending on your haste that should be plenty for ya into the high 50's.<br>
<br>
Spend that time saving for other weapons or building a list of folks to help you go after other items like the Ornate Sword and such.<br>
<br>
Good luck to ya..... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69785">Veteran Scartle SoulKlaw, Dwarven OverLord of Forlorn, E'CI Server</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scarsoulklaw>ScarSoulKlaw</A> at: 2/28/03 1:30:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krazrussian>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/28/03 5:45:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5150.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 52 DWF Warrior - I hate to do this...</span><hr size=1> Ornate Runed Sword of the General. Let me recap, Ornate Runed Sword of the General. in conclusion, Ornate Runed Sword of the General. 10/18 + stats and 35hp. drops 100% of the time off a mob that I have yet to see ever NOT up. Easy pull if you know the trick, get a good warrior, a chanter or shaman and a cleric, and tag along some DPS he'll drop like a rock. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wilhelmm D'averam<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Overlord of the Apocalypse</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
